Tom , I believe that your right up correctly interprets the current model , but as we discussed , I think the more correct methodology is to use the next day's cash price since the Gas Daily print is for gas traded the previous day and delivered the same day as the print . If I'm trading day gas on April 7th , the prices I'm basing my decisions on are those represented in the Gas Daily print for April 8th . If we do not change the model , I think we need another sentence to clarify that the cash prices a day behind . Of course , eventually we need to fix the model . Mat
