Swiss Atel Starts Electricity Derivative Trading Co Dow Jones International News ( Copyright ( c ) 1999 , Dow Jones & Company , Inc. ) ZURICH ( Dow Jones)--Aare-Tessin AG ( Z.AAR) , the Swiss power company known as Atel , said Thursday that it has set up a company for derivatives trading . Atel said it's launching the new company , derivAtel , amid the deregulation of Europe's electricity markets . "In this manner the market position of Atel will be strengthened," Atel said in a press release . The company will offer derivatives to hedge volatile electricity prices . Atel said it received permission for derivative trading from the Federal Banking Commission on July ( END ) Dow Jones Newswires 08-07-99
All Delaware corporations are registered with the Secretary of State's office in Wilmington , Delaware . Since that office is notoriously slow , if your counterparty is trying to get information on ECTRIC they might have better luck going through CT Corporation Systems , a company that is in the business of dealing with corporate information and issues which has access to the Delaware state records . They have offices all over the place , including Wilmington . Hope this is helpful . Mark Enron Capital & Trade Resources Corp . - Europe
