Hey Marc - I'm here - it's actually nice to be home & not traveling for a while . Will you guys be around this weekend ? It doesn't look like I can help your friend . We almost never hire lawyers fresh out of law school . Believe it or not , they don't really teach you how to be a lawyer in law school so passing the bar is just the first step . Your first job is where your real training takes place . We just don't have the time and capacity to train junior lawyers so we try to hire people who have worked for a number of years ( usually at least 5 or 6 ) at a good law firm . They get good training there and we don't have to hassle with it .
